        <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
      </header>
      <blockquote>Fight Club Monkey is a gaming clan that focuses more on having fun than winning the game.</blockquote>
      <p>Although we call ourselves a clan, we are more of a gaming social club, a group of friends that play games together.</p>
      <h3>What do you mean by gaming social club?</h3>
      <p>We feel that term describes us better than the word clan because of the activities we engage in. While most other clans exist purely for the game they play, we exist so that we can meet new people and enjoy ourselves while interacting with each another. While some of this interaction is within a game environment, it extends much further than this to include instant messaging, voice communications and chats in our Facebook group.</p>
      <p>This extends to when we are playing as well. Even when playing competitive games, we mind so much about winning or loosing (although winning is a great, but rare, treat), but rather about having a good time while we do it. We encourage people to chat while they play, ether using the game’s text chat support features, or using voice communications software (such as our TeamSpeak server). We often don’t like it when people stay silent.</p>
      <h3>Ethics</h3>
      <p>We have three main ethics that we use as a basis for our clan. Each of which is represented by one of the three triangles of the triforce on our shield:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respect for yourself and others.</li>
        <li>Friendship within the group and beyond.</li>
        <li>Enjoyment (it’s the reason we play the game in the first place).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We expect all our members to understand and respect our ethics, and to follow them at all times.</p>
